quran[67]{c,v,t}:
  90,1,I NEED not to swear by this SOIL
  90,2,This soil on which thou dost dwell
  90,3,Or by sire and offspring
  90,4,Surely in trouble have we created man
  90,5,What! thinketh he that no one hath power over him
  90,6,"I have wasted,\" saith he, \"enormous riches"
  90,7,What! thinketh he that no one regardeth him
  90,8,What! have we not made him eyes
  90,9,"And tongue, and lips"
  90,10,And guided him to the two highways
  90,11,Yet he attempted not the steep
  90,12,And who shall teach thee what the steep is
  90,13,It is to ransom the captive
  90,14,Or to feed in the day of famine
  90,15,The orphan who is near of kin
  90,16,or the poor that lieth in the dust
  90,17,"Beside this, to be of those who believe, and enjoin stedfastness on each other, and enjoin compassion on each other"
  90,18,These shall be the people of the right hand
  90,19,"While they who disbelieve our signs, Shall be the people of the left"
  90,20,Around them the fire shall close
  91,1,BY the SUN and his noonday brightness
  91,2,By the Moon when she followeth him
  91,3,By the Day when it revealeth his glory
  91,4,By the Night when it enshroudeth him
  91,5,By the Heaven and Him who built it
  91,6,By the Earth and Him who spread it forth
  91,7,By a Soul and Him who balanced it
  91,8,And breathed into it its wickedness and its piety
  91,9,Blessed now is he who hath kept it pure
  91,10,And undone is he who hath corrupted it
  91,11,Themoud in his impiety rejected the message of the Lord
  91,12,When the greatest wretch among them rushed up
  91,13,"Said the Apostle of God to them, - \"The Camel of God! let her drink"
  91,14,"But they treated him as an impostor and hamstrung her. So their Lord destroyed them for their crime, and visited all alike"
  91,15,Nor feared he the issue
  92,1,BY the NIGHT when she spreads her veil
  92,2,By the Day when it brightly shineth
  92,3,By Him who made male and female
  92,4,At different ends truly do ye aim
  92,5,But as to him who giveth alms and feareth God
  92,6,And yieldeth assent to the Good
  92,7,To him will we make easy the path to happiness
  92,8,But as to him who is covetous and bent on riches
  92,9,And calleth the Good a lie
  92,10,To him will we make easy the path to misery
  92,11,And what shall his wealth avail him when he goeth down
  92,12,Truly man's guidance is with Us
  92,13,"And Our's, the Future and the Past"
  92,14,I warn you therefore of the flaming fire
  92,15,None shall be cast to it but the most wretched
  92,16,Who hath called the truth a lie and turned his back
  92,17,But the God-fearing shall escape it
  92,18,Who giveth away his substance that he may become pure
  92,19,And who offereth not favours to any one for the sake of recompense
  92,20,But only as seeking the face of his Lord the Most High
  92,21,And surely in the end he shall be well content
  93,1,BY the noon-day BRIGHTNESS
  93,2,And by the night when it darkeneth
  93,3,"Thy Lord hath not forsaken thee, neither hath he been displeased"
  93,4,And surely the Future shall be better for thee than the Past
  93,5,And in the end shall thy Lord be bounteous to thee and thou be satisfied
  93,6,Did he not find thee an orphan and gave thee a home
  93,7,And found thee erring and guided thee
  93,8,And found thee needy and enriched thee
  93,9,As to the orphan therefore wrong him not
  93,10,"And as to him that asketh of thee, chide him not away"
  93,11,And as for the favours of thy Lord tell them abroad